### [Numbers Chapter 15](../../../bib/kjv/num015.htm#001.md)

[Numbers 15:2](../../../bib/kjv/num015.htm#002.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_002">num 15:2</span></span>

Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, When ye be come
into the (a) land of your habitations, which I give unto you,

\(a\) Into the land of Canaan.

[Numbers 15:4](../../../bib/kjv/num015.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">num 15:4</span></span>

Then shall he that offereth his offering unto the LORD bring a meat
offering of a tenth deal of flour mingled with the fourth \[part\] of an
(b) hin of oil.

\(b\) Read ([Exo 29:40](../../../bib/kjv/exo029.htm#040).md).

[Numbers 15:7](../../../bib/kjv/num015.htm#007.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_007">num 15:7</span></span>

And for a (c) drink offering thou shalt offer the third \[part\] of an
hin of wine, \[for\] a sweet savour unto the LORD.

\(c\) The liquor was so called, because it was poured on the thing that
was offered.

[Numbers 15:12](../../../bib/kjv/num015.htm#012.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_012">num 15:12</span></span>

According to the number (d) that ye shall prepare, so shall ye do to
every one according to their number.

\(d\) Every sacrifice of beasts must have their meat offering and drink
offering according to this proportion.

[Numbers 15:20](../../../bib/kjv/num015.htm#020.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_020">num 15:20</span></span>

Ye shall offer up a cake of the first of your (e) dough \[for\] an heave
offering: as \[ye do\] the heave offering of the threshingfloor, so
shall ye heave it.

\(e\) Which is made from the first corn you harvest.

[Numbers 15:22](../../../bib/kjv/num015.htm#022.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_022">num 15:22</span></span>

And if ye (f) have erred, and not observed all these commandments, which
the LORD hath spoken unto Moses,

\(f\) By oversight or ignorance, read ([Lev
4:2](../../../bib/kjv/lev004.htm#002.md), [Lev
4:13](../../../bib/kjv/lev004.htm#013).md).

[Numbers 15:31](../../../bib/kjv/num015.htm#031.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_031">num 15:31</span></span>

Because he hath despised the word of the LORD, and hath broken his
commandment, that soul shall utterly be cut off; his (h) iniquity
\[shall be\] upon him.

\(h\) He shall sustain the punishment of his sin.

[Numbers 15:39](../../../bib/kjv/num015.htm#039.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_039">num 15:39</span></span>

And it shall be unto you for a fringe, that ye may look upon it, and
remember all the commandments of the LORD, and do them; and that ye seek
not after your own heart and your own eyes, after which ye use to go a
(i) whoring:

\(i\) By leaving God's commandments and following your own fantasies.

